  16. (**

  18.    When diffing lists where each element has a distinct key, we can refine
  19.    the diffing patch by introducing two composite edit moves: swaps and moves.

  21.    [Swap]s exchange the position of two elements. [Swap] cost is set to
  22.    [2 * change - epsilon].
  23.    [Move]s change the position of one element. [Move] cost is set to
  24.    [delete + addition - epsilon].

  26.    When the cost [delete + addition] is greater than [change] and with those
  27.    specific weights, the optimal patch with [Swap]s and [Move]s can be computed
  28.    directly and cheaply from the original optimal patch.

  30. *)

  32. ‌type 'a with_pos = {pos: int; data:'a}
